post_text: Juneteenth is the oldest nationally celebrated commemoration of the ending of slavery in the United States. Dating back to 1865, it was on June 19th that the Union soldiers, led by Major General Gordon Granger, landed at Galveston, Texas with news that the war had ended and that the enslaved were now free. Note that this was two and a half years after President Lincoln‚Äôs Emancipation Proclamation - which had become official January 1, 1863. The Emancipation Proclamation had little impact on the Texans due to the minimal number of Union troops to enforce the new Executive Order. However, with the surrender of General Lee in April of 1865, and the arrival of General Granger‚Äôs regiment, the forces were finally strong enough to influence and overcome the resistance.

Note that this was two and a half years after President Lincoln‚Äôs Emancipation Proclamation - which had become official January 1, 1863. #Wellnesswednesday
Water is always the best choice.
Water should be the beverage that children (over age two) consume most frequently. Serve water with meals and snacks. For variety, try adding pieces of fresh fruit, vegetables, or fresh herbs to create a delicious alternative to plain water.
El agua es siempre la mejor opci√≥n.
El agua debe ser la bebida que los ni√±os (mayores de dos a√±os) consumen con mayor frecuencia. Sirva agua con las comidas y meriendas. Para variar, intente agregar trozos de fruta fresca, verduras o hierbas frescas para crear una alternativa deliciosa al agua corriente.

#Wellnesswednesday

Starting tomorrow every, Wednesday, Thursday, and Monday will be BOCS personalized #hashtag post. Mondays will be #Mybrainfoodmonday, Wednesdays will be #Wellnesswednesday, and last Thursday will be #Throwbackthursday. We are looking forward to providing you these beneficial gems and spicing up your news feed. Have a good rest of your day BOCS family.

A partir de ma√±ana todos los mi√©rcoles, jueves y lunes habr√° una publicaci√≥n #hashtag personalizada de BOCS. Los lunes ser√°n #Mybrainfoodmonday, los mi√©rcoles ser√°n #Wellnesswednesday, y el jueves pasado ser√° #Throwback jueves. Esperamos brindarle estas gemas beneficiosas y darle vida a sus noticias. post_text: Good evening everyone, we are happy to share that every Monday at 4pm will be "Coffee With The Principal". This will be a scheduled time that will share new information regarding the school (while in closure due to COVID-19), distance learning information, and of course a time for Q & A from you. You can join via URL link and/or phone (how to join provided on posted flyer above). If you have any questions or concerns please comment below and someone will respond to you ASAP. Thank you to all staff, students, family, friends, community supporters, and future advocates for all support you do for BOCS. Have a wonderful rest of your Thursday.

post_text:
Good afternoon families,

For today's daily video update please click this link.

In the update, I discuss when Chromebooks will be distributed. Please see the schedule below:

Day Time Grades
Monday, April 6th 9-11 a.m. TK, K, 1st, 6th
Tuesday, April 7th 9-11 a.m. 2nd, 3rd, 7th
Wednesday, April 8th 9-11 a.m. 4th, 5th

If you have multiple students, in different grades, you can still come just at one of the assigned days and receive devices for both students. If you were unable to pick up your student's learning packet, you can pick them up on your assigned date as well.

In order to pick up a device for your student, please bring your student with you. If that is not possible, a family member that is listed on the student's emergency card must be present to pick up the device and they must have a valid ID with a picture on it. Devices will be provided utilizing a drive through method. All families will be asked to stay in their cars during distribution.

Be well and be safe.

Best,

Mrs. Smith
